# Coding Standards & Workflow

## Code Quality Tools

### Linting & Formatting

- **Linter:** Biome (latest stable)
- **Formatter:** Biome formatter
- **Type Checker:** TypeScript strict mode

### Pre-Commit Checks

```bash
# Run before committing
bun run lint        # Biome check
bun run format      # Biome format
bun run typecheck   # TypeScript compiler
```

### Configuration

```json
// biome.json
{
  "$schema": "https://biomejs.dev/schemas/1.9.4/schema.json",
  "organizeImports": { "enabled": true },
  "linter": {
    "enabled": true,
    "rules": { "recommended": true }
  },
  "formatter": {
    "enabled": true,
    "indentStyle": "space",
    "indentWidth": 2
  }
}
```

## Git Workflow

### Commit Messages

Follow **Conventional Commits** format:

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>
```

### Commit Types

- `feat:` - New feature or section
- `fix:` - Bug fix
- `style:` - Styling changes (CSS, design tweaks)
- `refactor:` - Code refactoring
- `chore:` - Dependencies, config changes
- `docs:` - Documentation updates

### Examples

```
feat(hero): add animated code preview
style(features): improve card hover states
fix(waitlist): resolve form submission error
refactor(components): extract CodeBlock component
chore(deps): update TanStack Start to latest
```

### Branch Strategy

For a landing page, keep it simple:

- `main` - Production-ready code
- `feature/*` - Feature branches (new sections, major changes)
- `fix/*` - Bug fix branches

## File Naming Conventions

### Components

- Use kebab-case for files: `feature-card.tsx`, `code-block.tsx`
- Use PascalCase for exports: `export function FeatureCard() {}`

### Routes

- Follow TanStack Start conventions
- `__root.tsx` for root layout
- `index.tsx` for main page

### Assets

- Use descriptive names: `hero-code-preview.png`
- Use kebab-case: `og-image.png`, `favicon.ico`

## Component Guidelines

### File Structure

```typescript
// Imports (external, then internal, then types)
import { motion } from "framer-motion";
import { IconShield } from "@tabler/icons-react";

import { cn } from "~/lib/utils";

import type { FeatureProps } from "./types";

// Component
export function Feature({ title, description, icon }: FeatureProps) {
  return (
    // JSX
  );
}

// Keep component files focused - one main export per file
```

### Props Interface

```typescript
// Define props with TypeScript interfaces
interface FeatureCardProps {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  icon: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
}

// Use destructuring with defaults
export function FeatureCard({
  title,
  description,
  icon,
  className,
}: FeatureCardProps) {
  // ...
}
```

### Styling Patterns

```typescript
// Use cn() utility for conditional classes
import { cn } from "~/lib/utils";

function Button({ variant = "primary", className, ...props }) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        "px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors",
        variant === "primary" && "bg-primary text-primary-foreground",
        variant === "secondary" && "bg-card border border-border",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}
```

## Testing

### Manual Testing Checklist

For a landing page, focus on:

- [ ] All links work correctly
- [ ] Form submission works (waitlist)
- [ ] Responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- [ ] Animations don't cause jank
- [ ] Images load properly
- [ ] Fonts load correctly
- [ ] Page speed is acceptable
- [ ] Accessibility (keyboard nav, screen reader)

### Browser Testing

Test on:

- Chrome (primary)
- Firefox
- Safari
- Edge
- Mobile Safari (iOS)
- Chrome Mobile (Android)

## Performance Checklist

### Before Deployment

- [ ] Run Lighthouse audit (target: 90+ all categories)
- [ ] Check bundle size
- [ ] Verify image optimization
- [ ] Test on slow 3G throttling
- [ ] Check for layout shifts (CLS)

### Optimization Techniques

```typescript
// Lazy load below-fold images
<img loading="lazy" src="..." alt="..." />

// Use appropriate image formats
// Prefer WebP with fallbacks

// Preload critical fonts
<link rel="preload" href="/fonts/font.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossOrigin />
```

## Deployment

### Environment Variables

```bash
# .env.example
# Email service (optional)
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_AUDIENCE_ID=

# Analytics (optional)
PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=
```

### Vercel Deployment

```bash
# Install Vercel CLI
bun add -g vercel

# Deploy preview
vercel

# Deploy production
vercel --prod
```

### Pre-Deployment Checklist

- [ ] All environment variables set
- [ ] Build succeeds locally (`bun run build`)
- [ ] No TypeScript errors
- [ ] No console errors/warnings
- [ ] Meta tags and OG image configured
- [ ] Favicon in place
- [ ] robots.txt and sitemap configured
- [ ] Analytics configured (if applicable)

## Documentation

### Code Comments

- Comment complex logic or non-obvious code
- Use JSDoc for exported functions
- Keep comments up-to-date

```typescript
/**
 * Submits email to waitlist via server function.
 * Integrates with Resend if configured, otherwise logs to console.
 */
export const joinWaitlist = createServerFn({ method: "POST" })
  // ...
```

